
- *IMPORTANT*: When you have to reference a <step/>, use the following
  output <template/> (where <step-id/> correspondings to the `id="[...]"`
  XML attribute of the <step/> and <step-body/> correspondings to the XML
  body of the <step/>:

  <template>
  **<step-id/>**: <step-body/>
  </template>

- *IMPORTANT*: *Only* for <workflow strict/>,
  do *not* call `TaskCreate` tools in parallel, instead *wait* for each
  `TaskCreate` tool call to complete before proceeding with the next.

- *IMPORTANT*: *Only* for <workflow strict/>, use the `TaskUpdate` tool
  with its `addBlockedBy` parameter to ensure that all tasks are running
  in the given *chronological order*,
  i.e., `TaskUpdate({ taskId: "<id-of-step2/>", addBlockedBy: [ "<id-of-step-1/>" ] })`,
  i.e., `TaskUpdate({ taskId: "<id-of-step3/>", addBlockedBy: [ "<id-of-step-2/>" ] })`, etc.

